      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOPEFULLY FAST (2) flew the lids off the inside draw with a fast early split and gave a sight, finishing a 3.5 lengths second (21.72) over 380m at this track. Has a strong record from this draw, notching three wins and four minor placings from seven starts. Capable of going well again. TEX GUNN (7) was a last start winner this course and distance taking a Grade 4 in 21.48 in the best time on the card and clocking a personal best as well. Should be in this for a long way. MOUSTACHE MICK (1) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at this track over 498m behind Daniel Sparkles (29.40) in a Grade 4/5. Deserves plenty of respect. JIMMY JAX (3) has strong credentials over this journey.",
